        "content": "<p>I was using <a href=\"https://docs.rs/wasi/latest/wasi/fn.path_open.html\">wasi::path_open</a> on an existing file with the <code>wasi::OFLAGS_EXCL</code> oflag parameter, which should return an error if the file exists.<br>\nWhen I run the program with <code>wasmtime</code>, it returned <code>Ok()</code>, which I suppose not correct, right ?<br>\nI tried it with <code>wasmer</code> and it returned <code>wasi::ERRNO_EXIST</code> as I think it should.</p>\n<p>Here is the code I used <a href=\"https://github.com/Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite/tree/main/engines-diff/path-open-oflags\">here</a> </p>\n<p>Is this a bug in wasmtime, or I am missing something here ?</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite/tree/main/engines-diff/path-open-oflags\" style=\"background-image: url(https\\:\\/\\/uploads\\.zulipusercontent\\.net\\/e288bf2301ac20fa7739408e8e7f428a016991bc\\/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f326366343262373465353732366362646565613563613434366230373666306161626265656432343231643634383832343033313230643139623536363830632f4d6f2d46617461682f776173692d746573747375697465)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite/tree/main/engines-diff/path-open-oflags\" title=\"wasi-testsuite/engines-diff/path-open-oflags at main 路 Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite\">wasi-testsuite/engines-diff/path-open-oflags at main 路 Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Contribute to Mo-Fatah/wasi-testsuite development by creating an account on GitHub.</div></div></div>",
